    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-24T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-24T09:00:00-05:00" n="782"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1174</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d782fn1">Sent via the Embassy in France (No. 3094).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jassy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-24T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 26, 2.04 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. <persName corresp="#p_SGDG1">General Shcherbachev</persName>, chief of the
                    Ukrainian army, informed the Allied ministers confidentially this morning that
                    Ukrainia will sign separate peace with the Central powers within ten days on
                    very favorable terms. The Allied ministers will endeavor to have signing of such
                    a peace postponed on the ground that if Bolsheviks conclude peace for north
                    Russia such a peace would be useless to the Ukrainians and would not be
                    considered a friendly act towards the Allied powers.</p>
                <p>Your 128, January 21, 12 noon.<note n="2" xml:id="d782fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    Missing telegrams repeated immediately. Your telegrams 107 to 110 inclusive, 114
                    to 117 inclusive, 119 to 127 inclusive, missing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
